# BizPresence Pro — Cursor Rules

## Project Purpose
This is a config-driven corporate website template for DBCON INC.
All company content lives in `src/config/site.config.ts` — no hardcoding in components.

## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router, static export)
- TypeScript 5
- Tailwind CSS v4
- Lucide React icons
- Jest + React Testing Library

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript strictly — no `any`, no implicit types
- Functional components only — no class components
- Export default for page/section components
- Named exports for utilities and types
- Props interfaces defined inline or in `src/types/index.ts`
- Keep components focused — one responsibility per file

## Content Rules
- NEVER hardcode company name, contact, or content in components
- All text content must come from `siteConfig` imported from `@/config/site.config`
- To change company: edit `site.config.ts` only

## Styling Rules
- Use utility classes defined in `globals.css` first:
  - `.card` — standard dark card with subtle border
  - `.badge` — pill label for section headings
  - `.btn-primary` — solid blue CTA button
  - `.btn-ghost` — outline CTA button
  - `.tech-pill` — small technology tag
  - `.surface` — slightly lighter background section
  - `.divider` — horizontal gradient line
  - `.gradient-text` — blue-purple gradient text
- Avoid inline `style={{}}` except for dynamic color values
- No heavy glow effects or stacked gradients — keep it clean

## File Structure
```
src/
  app/           → Next.js pages (thin wrappers)
  components/
    layout/      → Header, Footer
    sections/    → Page section components
    ui/          → Reusable primitives
  config/        → site.config.ts (all content)
  types/         → TypeScript interfaces
__tests__/       → Jest tests mirroring src structure
```

## Testing
- Every section component must have a corresponding test file
- Use `data-testid` attributes for test targeting
- Tests import from `@/config/site.config` to stay config-driven
- Run: `npm test` before committing

## Deployment
- `npm run build` → generates `out/` folder (static HTML)
- `npm run deploy` → pushes `out/` to `gh-pages` branch
- GitHub Actions auto-deploys on push to `main`
- Live URL: https://yasshu317.github.io/dncon/
